    {
      "id": "PopularPost90160",
      "post_content": "I'm brewing something at the moment using this with the following: [Megrim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Megrim), [Howling Mine](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Howling Mine), [Underworld Dreams](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Underworld Dreams), [Burning Inquiry](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Burning Inquiry), [Sign in Blood](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sign in Blood), [Blightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blightning), [Mind Rot](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mind Rot), [Inquisition of Kozilek](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Inquisition of Kozilek), [Liliana Vess](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Liliana Vess) and [Liliana's Specter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Liliana's Specter), along plenty of burn like [Lighting Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lighting Bolt), [Burst Lighting](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Burst Lighting) and [Staggershock](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Staggershock), plus the obligatory [Doom Blade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade) and [Deathmark](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Deathmark) sideboards.   \n  \nNo creatures in main deck. [Back to Nature](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Back to Nature), [Naturalize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Naturalize), [War Priest of Thune](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=War Priest of Thune) and others of his Ilk are my main opposition, however the one card that completely shuts this kind of deck down is:   \n  \n\\*drumroll\\*  \n  \n[Leyline of Sanctity](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leyline of Sanctity)  \n  \nBack to the drawing ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
