      "post_content": "ALMOST strictly better than [Megrim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Megrim)  \nMegrim is costlier, which can make a big difference. Also, Megrim causes damage, while Caress causes life loss. In general, life loss is better, because it can't be prevented or redirected, but some cards (such as those with bloodthirst or [War Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=War Elemental)) get improvements from damage. So no, not strictly better, but in general, superior",
